     <actual value="2">
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">2016-2017: Multiple donors, partners and international organizations have adopted our Forecast-based Financing (FbF) concept. Many actors (such as IFRC, Ikea Foundation, FAO, WFP, Start Network) are implementing or funding this approach at different levels of intervention. In April 2017, the IFRC committed to set up a Preparedness Fund for Early Action triggered by forecasts. The Climate Centre is supporting the IFRC who committed to integrate Forecast based Financing (FbF) into the Disaster Risk Emergency Fund (DREF), hence IFRC is setting up a DREF-like fund to finance disasters ahead of time.
http://climatecentre.org/news/924/red-cross-red-crescent-pledge-on-climate-at-cop23-wea-ll-track-operational-scientific-and-policy-landscape-as-part-of-a-pivotal-rolea
We have worked with INCEIF, World Bank, DFRI and other Islamic Financing entities to ensure the need for funding early warning early action and explored the potential to use traditional instruments to support this work, such as &apos;takaful insurance-like instrument&apos; and &apos;WAQF charitable endowment&apos;. These discussions can help open up new channels of finance for the work that we and others do to reduce vulnerability. 
INsuresileince: layering on apprioprate resilience measures are part of it.
IFRC Framework for Climate Action</narrative>
